          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Intelligent Tutoring System",
          "Probability of getting the next candidate exercise correct",
          "Correct (1) vs Incorrect (0)",
          "3852 ASSISTments09 learners, 27485 ASSISTments12 learners nad 5000 EdNet learners",
          "ASSISTments & EdNet",
          "Answer sequences",
          "[HRG embeddings, SG embeddings]",
          "Graph-based KT has already been used. Current approaches either ignore relationship between exercises and skills. GIKT or PEBG-KT ignore relationships between exercises. \n\nAlso, all Graph KT models ignore the graph when answering questions.",
          "SGKT introduces 3 structures meant to address the flaws of the previous models:\n\nan HRG embedding which encodes the exercise-to-exercise and skill-to-skill information.\n\nAn SG embedding model which encodes the learner’s knowledge state.\n\nA prediction model which takes the previous representations and predicts the probability of getting the new exercise correctly.",
          "Both HRG and SG are combined using a self-attention mechanism.",
          "BKT, DKT, DKT+, KTM, DDKVMN, GIKT, SGKT",
          "Holdout Method",
          "AST09\n{AUC: 0.7975 - SGKT}\n\nAST12\n{AUC: 0.8135 - SGKT}\n\nEdNet\n{AUC: 0.7550 - SGKT}",
          "The authors create a new KT model based on Knowledge Graphs.\n\nThe model allows the measurement of the evolution of skills over time - interpretability.\n\nAuthors also do experiments to address cold-start scenario. SGKT ourperforms DKT and DKT+ on both of the scenarios tested - but eventually \n\n",
          "No cross-validation.\n\nLimited studies on cold-start scenarios.\n\nRequires model optimization efforts."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    }
  ],
