    {
      "id": "1954750c-f3ba-80d5-9e66-e8bd77b4ab51",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "LSTM is commonly used in DKT to analyze sequences of exercises done by students and predict whether the next exercise will be done right or not. However, LSTMs tend to give too much importance to short-term dependencies and often overlook longer-term dependencies. Authors look to create a Graph-Based Knowledge Model (SGKT). This model creates a representation for each exercise session and attempts to model the relationship between exercises and skills.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "1954750c-f3ba-80d5-9e66-e8bd77b4ab51",
        "parent": {
          "type": "page_id",
          "page_id": "18c4750c-f3ba-804e-81ee-e45b186197f5"
        },
        "created_time": "2025-02-09T00:12:00.000Z",
        "last_edited_time": "2025-02-09T00:24:00.000Z",
